<DESC>The Department of Commerce, National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration, Flower Garden Banks National Marine Sanctuary in Bryan TX requires services to repair a vessel, the Point Glass.  Detailed specifications contain the requirements for haul-out and repairs.  All work requiring the ship to be hauled out will be performed at the contractors facility.  Dockside work may be performed at the contractors facility or along side the NOAA Facility in Freeport TX.  The Point Glass is an EX-USCG Point-Class Cutter with the following measurements:  Length overall 82 ft 10 in; beam 17ft 7 in; depth 12 ft c in; max draft 5ft 9 in; GRT 116.7T; displacement 67 long tons. The basic work will include haul out; UT test; underwater hull painting; fuel tank cleaning; sea valve and strainer overhaul; bilge pump overhaul and suction installation; shaft removal, inspection and maintenance; zinc renewal and remove and balance propellers.  Optional items include potable water tank cleaning and painting; prepare, prime, and paint engine room bilges; renew rudder packing and cutlass bearing; shell plate renewal; pressure test and float coat voids.  The vessel is available for pre-bid inspection by prospective contractors at the NOAA facility in Freeport TX.  Contact Capt Ken Daniels at (979) 777-9515 for directions and to schedule an appointment to view the vessel.  A request for quote (RFQ) which includes all required specifications may be available by August 31, 2004.  The period allowed for submitting quotes will be limited.  Firms interested in receiving the RFQ should fax their request to (816) 426-5067, Attention Sharon Clisso or e-mail Ms. Clisso at sharon.k.clisso@noaa.gov no later than  August  30, 2004.  Requests should reference number NCND6011400019SKC.  PHONE REQUESTS WILL NOT BE ACCEPTED.  This acquisition is intended to be conducted pursuant to the guidelines set forth in FAR Part 12 for Commercial Acquisitions and FAR Part 13 for Simplified Acquisitions.  The DOC 