<DESC>The Department of Commerce, National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration, Flower Garden Banks National Marine Sanctuary in Bryan TX requires services of the Tennessee Aquarium to design, develop and maintain a set of interactive stations to interpret the Flower Garden Banks National Marine Sanctuary programs and trust resources.  The stations will complement the one-half million gallon tank modeled after the Flower Garden Banks in the new wing of the Tennessee Aquarium, schedule to open in the Spring of 2005.  The Tennessee Aquarium will design and develop software and content for the interactive program based on specific topics, possible animations, graphics, video clips, etc; purchase hardware for six stations plus one back-up; secure use rights for still and video images to illustrate content; construct appropriate housing and mounting structures for installation of hardware in the exhibit at the aquarium.  The Flower Garden Banks National Marine Sanctuary partners with a variety of non-governmental organizations that have missions compatible with the sanctuary’s mandates. This effort is part of the development of a partnership with the Tennessee Aquarium.  The partnership is necessary in order for sanctuary staff to reach vast numbers of the public that interact with the aquarium each year.  The aquarium is expanding the facility.  The centerpiece of the expansion is the one half million gallon tank modeled after the Flower Garden Banks.  The Government plans to request a quote from only one source,  Tennessee Aquarium,  for this requirement  under the authority of FAR 6.302 and following the guidelines in FAR Part 12 Commercial Acquisitions and FAR Part 13 Simplified Acquisitions.   Interested persons may identify their interest and capability to respond to the requirement or submit quotes. This notice of intent is not a request for competitive quotes.  However, all responses received within 15 days after date of publication of this synopsis will be co