GENERAL REQUIREMENTS:

The Federal Bureau of Prisons (BOP), United States Penitentiary (USP) McCreary, located at 330 Federal Way, Pine Knot, Kentucky, has a requirement for a Metal Building award is estimated to be on or about August 26.  The successful contractor shall deliver the materials within 30 working days of the award. 

The building must be metal with a steel beam framing in the following dimensions: 60 feet wide by a 150 feet long by 20 feet high eave height.  The building must have a metal roof with a minimum of 24 gauge metal and a 1/12 roof pitch.  The roof also must be Natural Patina or Aged Copper in color.  The building must contain 12= 3 x 10 light panels with trip kits.  The metal sides of the building must be a minimum of 26 gauge . The building must contain a minimum of a 20 year warranty.   All included is the gutter package a 1= 12 foot by 18 foot commercial series roll up door with a chain hoist and top header seal.  The building must contain two (2) 3 foot insulated doors keyed alike and insulated roof and walls.

SUPPLIES:

The contractor shall provide the following supplies:

A 60 foot wide by a 150 foot long by a 20 foot high, eave height, metal building with a steel beam framing.

